04:22.929 --> 04:25.193
But it's me, Moe,
wearing a sailor suit.

04:25.298 --> 04:27.357
Moe with a lolly.
[ Chuckles ]

04:27.467 --> 04:30.197
It's so out of character.
Ain't that worth nothin'?

04:30.303 --> 04:33.136
- <i>[ Booing ]</i>
- <i>[ Woman ] Come on. Next.</i>

04:33.239 --> 04:35.469
All right,judges,
who is our winner?

04:35.575 --> 04:37.133
The winner is...

04:37.243 --> 04:39.643
me for being seen with you freaks.

04:39.746 --> 04:42.977
Judges can't win the contest! Boo!

04:43.082 --> 04:46.950
You have robbed us of our dignity.

04:47.053 --> 04:49.749
Well, you- [ Gasps ]
A urinal cake!

04:49.856 --> 04:52.950
You, sir, have crossed the line.

04:53.059 --> 04:54.890
Oy!

04:54.994 --> 04:57.554
<i>[ Crowd Shouting ]</i>

04:57.664 --> 05:00.531
<i>People, stop, stop.!</i>
<i>We're not animals.!</i>

05:00.633 --> 05:03.602
[ Ape Calls ]

05:06.506 --> 05:08.406
Take that!

05:10.910 --> 05:12.605
[ All Cheering ]

05:12.712 --> 05:14.805
[ Groans, Gasps ]

05:14.914 --> 05:16.848
[ Moans, Gasps ]

05:21.387 --> 05:23.855
An open letter
to the people of Springfield.

05:23.956 --> 05:27.255
Today, our town lost what remained
of its fragile civility...

05:27.360 --> 05:29.521
drowned in a sea
of low fat pudding.

05:29.629 --> 05:32.860
- Look, I got runner-up prize.
- You won second place?

05:32.965 --> 05:34.933
No, but I got it.

05:35.968 --> 05:37.936
Stealing is wrong.

05:38.037 --> 05:40.904
''Free boudoir photography.''

05:41.007 --> 05:42.975
Sweet!

05:46.346 --> 05:48.211
Hmm.

05:48.314 --> 05:51.340
[ Mutters, Gasps ]

05:51.451 --> 05:53.681
Oh, right.

05:53.786 --> 05:57.779
We are a town of lowbrows,
no brows and ignorami.

05:57.890 --> 06:00.620
We have eight malls,
but no symphony.

06:00.727 --> 06:03.491
Thirty-two bars,
but no alternative theater.

06:03.596 --> 06:06.622
Thirteen stores
that begin with ''Le Sex.''

06:06.733 --> 06:10.328
I write this letter not to nag
or whine, but to prod.

06:10.436 --> 06:12.336
We can better ourselves.

06:12.438 --> 06:14.201
- [ Pig Squealing ]
- Yeehaw!

06:14.307 --> 06:16.275
Well, most of us.

06:20.713 --> 06:23.147
Dad, did you see anything provocative
in today's paper?

06:23.249 --> 06:26.412
Yes, there's a real think piece
here about a bra sale.

06:26.519 --> 06:29.750
Dad, stop kidding around.
Look. They printed my letter.

06:29.856 --> 06:32.791
Hey, that is wonderful, sweetie.
I'm gonna read it...

06:32.892 --> 06:35.759
just as soon as I finish
what I'm doing here.

06:38.765 --> 06:41.563
Well, I'm sure someone
had the time to read it.

06:41.667 --> 06:43.567
I envy them.

06:43.669 --> 06:45.534
Hi, Mr. Flanders.

06:45.638 --> 06:48.198
I see you're reading the newspaper.

06:48.307 --> 06:50.366
[ Chuckles ]
Everything but the opinion page.

06:50.476 --> 06:53.843
I don't need to be told what to think...
by anyone living.

06:53.946 --> 06:55.914
Chief Wiggum.

06:56.015 --> 06:59.280
Oh, you sure got
a lot of copies of the paper.

06:59.385 --> 07:01.615
Yeah, I need to housebreak
our new police dog.

07:01.721 --> 07:05.179
Plus, it couldn't hurt Ralphie
to brush up on the fundamentals.

07:05.291 --> 07:08.556
Daddy says I'm this close
to living in the yard.

07:08.661 --> 07:11.391
[ Groans ]
Doesn't anybody in this town read?

07:11.497 --> 07:13.397
Oh, hello, Lisa.

07:13.499 --> 07:16.798
Can you recommend any books
for my mobile?

07:16.903 --> 07:20.839
Oh, absolutely. Well, you know,
anything byJane Austen.

07:20.940 --> 07:24.137
Jane Austen. Thanks, Lisa.
I'll get right on it.

07:29.582 --> 07:32.415
[ Gasps ]

07:32.518 --> 07:34.418
''We read your letter
with great interest.

07:34.520 --> 07:37.785
''If you wish to learn more,
go to 1 3 Euclid street.

07:37.890 --> 07:41.291
Tell no one.
And bring a dessert.''

07:41.394 --> 07:43.726
- Oooh.
- <i>[ Bart ] Hey, Lise.</i>

07:43.830 --> 07:46.025
- [ Squealing ]
- Whoa! Whoa!

07:48.768 --> 07:51.999
- <i>[ Bell Chiming ]</i>
- <i>[ Male Voice, Deep ] Lisa Simpson...</i>

07:52.104 --> 07:56.598
<i>are you ready to go on a voyage</i>
<i>of intellectual self-discovery?</i>

07:56.709 --> 07:58.108
I think so.

07:58.211 --> 08:00.771
<i>Is that a pie or a quiche?</i>

08:00.880 --> 08:03.644
- A pie.
- <i>[ Voices Chattering ]</i>

08:03.749 --> 08:06.240
<i>You may enter.</i>

08:06.352 --> 08:09.810
- [ Gasps ]
- Welcome to Mensa, Lisa!

08:09.922 --> 08:12.550
It's the organization
for people with high I.Q.'s.

08:12.658 --> 08:16.651
I know that. It's also a constellation visible
only from the southern hemisphere.

08:16.762 --> 08:19.026
She's good.
She's very good.

08:19.131 --> 08:21.964
[ Laughs ]
And she brought a cream pie.

08:25.605 --> 08:27.869
You want me to join Mensa?

08:27.974 --> 08:31.273
Oh, that's wonderful. But don't I have
to take some sort of I.Q. test?

08:31.377 --> 08:33.277
No, Lisa, you're more than qualified.

08:33.379 --> 08:36.075
I shared all your standardized
test scores with the other members.

08:36.182 --> 08:39.447
- Aren't those supposed to be confidential?
- Welcome to Mensa!

08:39.552 --> 08:42.214
You've joined such luminaries
as cartoonist, Mel Lazarus...

08:42.321 --> 08:46.087
Geena Davis and <i>Parade</i> magazine's
Marilyn vos Savant.

08:46.192 --> 08:48.217
Each the tops
in his or her field...

08:48.327 --> 08:50.557
uh, except for Mel Lazarus.

08:50.663 --> 08:52.494
Wow. I'm so honored
you wanted me.

08:52.598 --> 08:56.364
Well, it was your delightfully condescending
letter that put you over the top.

08:56.469 --> 08:59.802
- Lindsay Neagle, Advanced Capital Ventures.
- Oh, what do you produce?

08:59.906 --> 09:02.170
Synergy, and books
on how to cheat at bridge.

09:02.275 --> 09:04.266
Lisa, I think you'll
really enjoy it here.

09:04.377 --> 09:07.676
Now, let's get down to business.
Any new palindromes?

09:07.780 --> 09:10.647
[ Clears Throat ]
Rise to vote, sir.

09:10.750 --> 09:14.686
Now, you know the agenda. Palindromes,
anagrams, eat Lisa's pie, then voting.

09:14.787 --> 09:17.312
But ''rise to vote, sir'' is a palindrome.

09:17.423 --> 09:19.323
- Good glavin. She's right.
- Told you.

09:19.425 --> 09:22.053
Lisa, I think you're gonna fit
in just fine around here.

09:23.296 --> 09:25.730
Wow. Me, fit in.

09:34.941 --> 09:39.674
Hello. I have a certificate
for a free erotic photo session.

09:39.779 --> 09:44.273
- Oh, yes. Your name?
- Uh, Geraldo Simpson.

09:44.383 --> 09:46.476
- All right, Mr. Simpson-
- [ Screams ] Who told you?

09:46.586 --> 09:49.020
Don't worry.
These photos are perfectly legal.

09:49.121 --> 09:51.954
Many husbands use them
as a romantic gift for their wives.

09:52.058 --> 09:55.425
Uh, you're not gonna ask me
to pose nude, are you?

09:55.528 --> 09:58.793
Well, yes, unless you have
some issues with revealing your body.

09:58.898 --> 10:01.924
Well, I don't,
but the block association seems to.

10:02.034 --> 10:05.162
They wanted
a ''traditional'' Santa Claus.

10:05.271 --> 10:06.795
<i>##[ Classical ]</i>

10:06.906 --> 10:09.875
I can't believe how they're dumbing
down the Springfield Library.

10:09.976 --> 10:12.137
They've gotten rid
of the English literature section...

10:12.244 --> 10:15.304
and replaced it with
a make-your-own-sundae bar.

10:15.414 --> 10:18.906
I heard they got rid of the reference desk
to make room for an air hockey table.

10:19.018 --> 10:22.385
- Even the microfilm?
- Even the microfiche.

10:22.488 --> 10:26.151
- [ All Moan ]
- My family never talks about library standards.

10:26.258 --> 10:29.091
And every time I try to steer
the conversation that way...

10:29.195 --> 10:31.095
they make me feel
like a nerd.

10:31.197 --> 10:34.826
We are hardly nerds. Would a nerd
wear such an irreverent sweatshirt?

10:34.934 --> 10:37.368
<i>[ Lisa Reading ]</i>

10:39.238 --> 10:41.365
Oh, only one person
in a million would find that funny.

10:41.474 --> 10:43.601
Yes, we call that
the Dennis Miller ratio.

10:50.349 --> 10:52.749
Oh, Dad, I just spent the day
with the most wonderful people.

10:52.852 --> 10:57.050
Oh, that's great, honey. You tell me everything
you can before the commercial's over.

10:57.156 --> 11:01.092
- For the first time in my life,
I feel that someone understand-
- Bup, bup, bup, bup.

11:03.362 --> 11:05.262
Are you ready in there,
Mr. Simpson?

11:05.364 --> 11:08.333
<i>Are you sure you're a fully accredited</i>
<i>and bonded pornographer?</i>

11:08.434 --> 11:10.334
Just come out.

11:10.436 --> 11:14.133
- Please be kind.
- <i>You look fantastic.</i>

11:14.240 --> 11:16.105
Let me just adjust my lens here.

11:18.210 --> 11:21.407
Now you're sure
this will save my marriage?

11:21.514 --> 11:23.812
Try not to speak.
It's making your body ripple.

11:23.916 --> 11:26.316
Hmm.
[ Grunts, Groans ]

11:26.419 --> 11:28.751
- [ Shudders ]
- <i>##[ Humming ]</i>

11:28.854 --> 11:30.845
- <i>[ Bart ] Dad? Dad, are you home?</i>
- <i>[ Knocking ]</i>

11:30.956 --> 11:33.447
[ Gasps, Grunts ]

11:33.559 --> 11:35.527
[ Grunts, Groans ]

11:35.628 --> 11:38.062
<i>Fine.! I don't care</i>
<i>what you're doing.!</i>

11:38.164 --> 11:40.257
[ Sighs, Screams ]

11:42.668 --> 11:44.568
<i>Don't look.! Don't look.!</i>
<i>Don't look.!</i>

11:44.670 --> 11:47.230
Okay, I think he's gone.

11:47.339 --> 11:49.239
Let's reschedule.

11:51.177 --> 11:54.544
This is so cool. I feel like I'm back
in the Renaissance.

11:54.647 --> 11:56.638
Please stay in character,
gentle wench.

11:56.749 --> 11:59.582
Verily I declare that the Earth
revolves around the sun...

11:59.685 --> 12:01.744
and not t'other way around.

12:01.854 --> 12:04.049
Stop looking down
my blouse, Copernicus.

12:04.156 --> 12:07.182
Forsooth. Mine eyes doth rove
of their own accord.

12:07.293 --> 12:10.091
Zounds!
Someone took our gazebo!

12:11.530 --> 12:14.192
No, no, that's impossible.
We reserved it months ago.

12:14.300 --> 12:16.200
Someone should
stand up to them.

12:16.302 --> 12:17.929
- Oh, dear.
- Hmm.

12:18.037 --> 12:20.267
I'll do it.

12:20.372 --> 12:24.172
Excuse me, gentlemen. Might I take a peak
at your gazebo reservation form?

12:24.276 --> 12:27.768
- Beat it!
- [ Chuckles ] Yes, well, we each have a good case.

12:27.880 --> 12:29.905
What part of''beat it''
didn't you understand?

12:30.015 --> 12:32.381
Hmm, I guess it would be the ''it.''

12:32.485 --> 12:36.319
I'm not exactly sure to what
that refers. It's- Ow!

12:36.422 --> 12:40.586
Oh, it's hopeless. There are some
she-males in gazebo three...

12:40.693 --> 12:43.025
a nasty looking spider
in gazebo six...

12:43.129 --> 12:45.723
and the less said about gazebo eight,
the better.

12:45.831 --> 12:47.822
Ah, Chief, thank God you're here.

12:47.933 --> 12:50.424
We reserved gazebo seven,
and look.

12:50.536 --> 12:53.937
Geez. How many gazebos
do you she-males need?

12:55.374 --> 12:57.740
Beer me, boys.

12:57.843 --> 13:00.607
Why do we live in a town
where the smartest have no power...

13:00.713 --> 13:02.613
and the stupidest run everything?

13:02.715 --> 13:04.683
- Maybe I should just move back to Alabama.
- No.

13:04.784 --> 13:09.244
We should fix things here. If we put our minds to it,
there's no limit to what we can accomplish.

13:09.355 --> 13:12.688
- I think the girl's right.
- Good point.

13:17.062 --> 13:19.690
- The jig is up, Quimby.
- Oh, God!

13:19.799 --> 13:23.963
When you see what's in this report,
things are going to change in this town.

13:24.069 --> 13:26.333
- I earned that lotto money. I swear.
- [ Buzzing ]

13:32.378 --> 13:34.903
- Hyah!
- [ Horse Neighs ]

13:35.014 --> 13:37.073
Faster, you moron.

13:39.585 --> 13:42.520
[ Neighs ]

13:42.621 --> 13:44.452
Oh. Well, that was unexpected.

13:44.557 --> 13:47.048
- [ Guns Cocking ]
- What's going on? Where's the mayor?

13:47.159 --> 13:49.423
- He skipped town.
- Really?

13:49.528 --> 13:51.758
So, who's in charge?

13:51.864 --> 13:56.233
Well, that's a good question. Let's, uh, take
a quick look at the town charter.

13:58.704 --> 14:01.867
- [ All ] Done.
- Finished.

14:01.974 --> 14:04.101
According to the charter,
''should the mayor abdicate...

14:04.210 --> 14:07.407
a council of learned citizens
may rule in his stead.''

14:07.513 --> 14:09.538
Well, there's no one
more learned than us.

14:09.648 --> 14:12.811
So, I guess... we're in charge.

14:12.918 --> 14:15.443
What!
Let me see that.

14:15.554 --> 14:19.752
Let's see here. ''We the people,''
''cruel and unusual,'' blah, blah, blah.

14:19.859 --> 14:21.952
''Ritual circumcision,''
yak, yak, yak.

14:22.061 --> 14:24.086
Ah, geez,
I'll take your word for it.

14:24.196 --> 14:27.131
- I guess you are in charge.
- [ Cheering ]

14:27.233 --> 14:29.133
With our superior intellects...

14:29.235 --> 14:32.568
we could rebuild this city on a foundation
of reason and enlightenment.

14:32.671 --> 14:34.798
We could turn Springfield
into a utopia.

14:34.907 --> 14:37.501
- A new Athens.
- Or Walden Two.

14:37.610 --> 14:39.908
Yeah, a real Candy Land!

14:40.946 --> 14:43.414
Of the mind. The mind.

14:43.515 --> 14:45.949
I'll just go now.
Bunch of dorks.

14:47.920 --> 14:50.184
<i>This is Kent Brockman at City Hall...</i>

14:50.289 --> 14:52.723
where the intellectual junta
known as the ''Bright Pack''...

14:52.825 --> 14:55.385
has been running this town
for the better part of three days.

14:55.494 --> 14:57.985
[ Chattering ]

14:58.097 --> 15:01.498
So, Lisa, what do you and your fellow
eggheads have planned for the city?

15:01.600 --> 15:03.500
- Business as usual?
- No, Kent.

15:03.602 --> 15:06.935
We're gonna use the power of good ideas
to change things for the better.

15:07.039 --> 15:10.065
Well, excuse this jaded reporter
if he says he's heard that before.

15:10.175 --> 15:12.769
- Oh, well, we really mean it.
- [ Gasps ] You do?

15:12.878 --> 15:15.847
Yes. For example, no one
was showing up for jury duty.

15:15.948 --> 15:18.041
So we made the experience
more exciting...

15:18.150 --> 15:20.380
by synergizing it
with his comic book collection.

15:22.087 --> 15:24.851
''You have been chosen
to join theJustice Squadron...

15:24.957 --> 15:29.189
8:00 a.m. Monday at the Municipal
Fortress of Vengeance.''

15:29.295 --> 15:30.887
Oh, I am so there.

15:30.996 --> 15:32.930
We studied traffic patterns
and found that...

15:33.032 --> 15:35.899
drivers move the fastest
through yellow lights.

15:36.001 --> 15:41.439
So now, we just have the red
and yellow lights. [ Chuckles ]

15:44.743 --> 15:48.440
Come on.
Stay yellow. Stay yellow!

15:48.547 --> 15:52.313
Man, I'm making record time,
if only I had someplace to be.

15:52.418 --> 15:56.047
And we've really elevated the level
of discourse at the dog track.

15:56.155 --> 15:59.454
<i>We replaced the fanfare</i>
<i>with classical music.</i>

15:59.558 --> 16:02.356
<i>And instead of chasing a rabbit,</i>
<i>the dogs chase a diploma.</i>

16:02.461 --> 16:03.985
[ Barking ]

16:04.096 --> 16:06.656
The world has already taken note
of our accomplishments.

16:06.765 --> 16:09.325
Springfield has moved up
to number 299...

16:09.435 --> 16:12.461
on the list of America's
300 most livable cities.

16:12.571 --> 16:14.664
Take that, East St. Louis.

16:17.009 --> 16:21.503
Gee. You said you were gonna make me
look sexier, but it's awfully dark in here.

16:21.613 --> 16:25.344
Light is not your friend.
All right, let's do this thing.

16:25.451 --> 16:28.579
- <i>##[ Dance Rock ]</i>
- It's time to get Homer-erotic!

16:28.687 --> 16:30.712
- [ Shudders ]
- <i>[ Camera Shutter Clicking ]</i>

16:34.560 --> 16:38.087
<i>Okay, next item ofbusiness</i>
<i>is our weekly progress report.</i>

16:38.197 --> 16:40.529
Principal Skinner, how's your
transportation project coming?

16:40.632 --> 16:43.726
Oh, excellent. Not only are
the trains now running on time...

16:43.836 --> 16:45.736
they're running on metric time.

16:45.838 --> 16:49.274
Remember this moment, people-
80 past 2:00 on April 47 th.

16:49.375 --> 16:52.071
It's the dawn of
an enlightened Springfield.

16:52.177 --> 16:55.544
Excellent. Now, next week
is our state of the city address.

16:55.647 --> 16:57.581
Has everyone finalized
their proposals?

16:57.683 --> 17:01.119
Well, first of all, I have a plan to eliminate
obesity... in females.

17:01.220 --> 17:03.484
Oh, please. For a nickel
a person tax increase...

17:03.589 --> 17:05.614
we could build a theater
for shadow puppets.

17:05.723 --> 17:09.125
- Balinese or Thai?
- Why not both? Then everybody's happy.

17:09.228 --> 17:11.423
Oh, yeah.
Everyone's real happy then!

17:11.530 --> 17:13.589
Do I detect a note of sarcasm?

17:13.699 --> 17:17.066
Are you kidding me? This baby is off the charts.
[ Chuckles ]

17:17.169 --> 17:20.332
- Oh, a sarcasm detector.
That's a real useful invention.
- <i>[ Beeping Rapidly ]</i>

17:21.773 --> 17:23.867
[ All Arguing ]

17:23.976 --> 17:26.467
<i>[ Homer ]</i>
<i>Marge. Oh, Marge.</i>

17:26.578 --> 17:29.979
I've got something for you.

17:30.082 --> 17:33.279
- Oh, Homie.
- <i>Houston, we have a problem.</i>

17:33.385 --> 17:35.478
A sexy problem.

17:35.587 --> 17:38.681
Homie. Well, look at you.

17:38.791 --> 17:41.521
<i>[ Growling ]</i>
<i>I'm gonna maul you.</i>

17:41.627 --> 17:44.118
Homer, I've never
seen this side of you.

17:44.229 --> 17:46.959
But I like it.

17:50.169 --> 17:52.865
Whoo, whoa.
Look at those silk pillows.

17:52.971 --> 17:55.439
It's like the set
of some high-class porno film.

17:55.541 --> 17:58.442
No, no.
It's just our basement.

17:58.544 --> 18:00.603
[ Groans ]
Hold on! Wait.

18:00.712 --> 18:02.680
That's our basement?

18:02.781 --> 18:05.079
Yeah. So? Come on.
More kissing.

18:05.184 --> 18:10.087
It looks so elegant. And all it takes are
some lace curtains and a beaded lampshade.

18:10.189 --> 18:12.248
You've got to show me
exactly what you did.

18:12.357 --> 18:14.917
- But I was gonna score.
- No, you weren't.

18:16.695 --> 18:19.095
Welcome, everyone!
Today, we embark...

18:19.198 --> 18:21.689
on a new era
of intelligent governance.

18:21.800 --> 18:24.132
[ Chanting ]
Governance! Governance!

18:24.236 --> 18:26.602
- <i>Governance.!</i>
- [ Microphone Feeds Back ]

18:26.705 --> 18:28.969
[ Clears Throat ]
We have some new rules and regulations...

18:29.074 --> 18:31.133
that you're gonna just
go ape poopy over.

18:31.243 --> 18:33.939
- Professor Frink.
- [ Clears Throat ] Well, first of all...

18:34.046 --> 18:37.709
we're going to ban such barbaric sports
as bullfighting and cockfighting.

18:37.816 --> 18:39.875
[ Cheering ]

18:39.985 --> 18:43.477
Also, boxing, both kick
and the kind with the gloves.

18:43.589 --> 18:46.217
- [ Woman ] Good!
- And hockey, football, push-ups...

18:46.325 --> 18:50.022
and anything in general where you have to
take off your shirt, which is embarrassing.

18:50.129 --> 18:52.723
- [ All Murmuring Disagreement ]
- I don't remember discussing that.

18:52.831 --> 18:57.962
Inspired by the most logical race
in the galaxy, the Vulcans...

18:58.070 --> 19:00.766
breeding will be permitted
once every seven years.

19:00.873 --> 19:03.364
- [ All Gasp ]
- <i>For many of you,</i>
<i>this will mean much less breeding.</i>

19:03.475 --> 19:05.272
For me, much, much more.

19:05.377 --> 19:08.710
Ya cannot do that, sir!
Ya don't have the power!

19:08.814 --> 19:10.975
Ladies and gentlemen,
I must apologize.

19:11.083 --> 19:13.381
This man does not speak
for the Council of Alphas.

19:13.485 --> 19:15.953
We hold you subomeguloids
in the highest regard.

19:16.054 --> 19:18.249
When are we gonna get
to my broccoli juice program?

19:18.357 --> 19:21.121
Quit butting in, please.
Your I.Q. is a mere 1 5 5...

19:21.226 --> 19:23.057
while mine is a muscular 1 7 0.

19:23.162 --> 19:24.720
[ Singsongy ]
I am smart.

19:24.830 --> 19:27.264
Much smarter than you, Hibbert!

19:27.366 --> 19:31.666
You should all do what I say.
My I.Q. is 1 99, for crying out glavin.

19:31.770 --> 19:34.398
[ Groans ]
1 98. 1 97.

19:34.506 --> 19:37.475
<i>[ Computerized Voice ]</i>
<i>Big deal. My I.Q. is 280.</i>

19:37.576 --> 19:39.908
[ All Gasp ]

19:40.012 --> 19:41.809
[ Together]
Stephen Hawking!

19:41.914 --> 19:44.712
- The world's smartest man!
- What are you doing here?

19:44.816 --> 19:47.182
[ Computerized Voice ]
I wanted to see your utopia.

19:47.286 --> 19:49.914
But now I see it is
more of a Fruitopia.

19:50.022 --> 19:53.753
- I'm sure what Dr. Hawking means is-
- <i>Silence.</i>

19:53.859 --> 19:57.818
I don't need anyone to talk for me,
except this voice box.

19:57.930 --> 20:01.161
You have clearly been
corrupted by power. For shame!

20:01.266 --> 20:03.700
Larry Flynt is right!
You guys stink!

20:03.802 --> 20:06.396
[ All Shouting Agreement ]

20:06.505 --> 20:09.269
I don't know which is
a bigger disappointment-

20:09.374 --> 20:12.741
<i>my failure to formulate</i>
<i>a unified field theory, or you.</i>

20:12.844 --> 20:14.709
I don't like your tone.

20:14.813 --> 20:17.509
If you are looking for trouble,
you found it.

20:17.616 --> 20:19.846
Yeah,just try me, you-
[ Screams ]

20:19.952 --> 20:22.386
- [ All Cheering ]
- Now's our opening!

20:22.487 --> 20:25.251
Come on, you idiots!
We're taking back this town!

20:25.357 --> 20:27.757
Yeah! Let's make litter
out of these literati!

20:27.859 --> 20:30.327
That's too clever.
You're one of them!

20:30.429 --> 20:32.192
[ All Shouting ]

20:32.297 --> 20:34.231
Please stay calm everyone.

20:35.934 --> 20:37.333
[ Screams ]

20:37.436 --> 20:39.927
Time for this Hawk to fly.

20:41.873 --> 20:43.738
Wrong button.

20:49.581 --> 20:51.446
[ Lisa ]
Help!

21:01.526 --> 21:03.824
Lisa, thank God you're okay.

21:03.929 --> 21:07.092
- Did you have fun with your robot buddy?
- Dad!

21:07.199 --> 21:11.533
Oh, Dr. Hawking, we had such
a beautiful dream. What went wrong?

21:11.637 --> 21:13.332
<i>Don't feel bad, Lisa.</i>

21:13.438 --> 21:17.033
Sometimes the smartest of us
can be the most childish.

21:17.142 --> 21:20.737
- Even you?
- No, not me. Never.

21:20.846 --> 21:24.077
I guess everyone has a different vision
for the perfect world.

21:24.182 --> 21:26.150
Wow, Mom,
that's very profound.

21:26.251 --> 21:28.344
Hey, you read that off my screen.

21:29.388 --> 21:31.083
- Who's up for some beers?
- I am!

21:31.189 --> 21:33.680
That's the smartest thing
I've heard all day.

21:35.360 --> 21:39.456
Your theory of a doughnut-shaped
universe is intriguing, Homer.

21:39.564 --> 21:41.464
I may have to steal it.

21:41.566 --> 21:44.433
Wow. I can't believe
someone I never heard of...

21:44.536 --> 21:46.436
is hanging out
with a guy like me.

21:46.538 --> 21:49.098
All right, it's closing time.
Who's paying the tab?

21:49.207 --> 21:51.573
- <i>[ Homer, Monotone ] I am.</i>
- I didn't say that.

21:51.677 --> 21:54.475
Yes, I did. D'oh.

22:40.959 --> 22:44.725
- Shh!
